  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Localize Date Formatting Based on Language Selection\n\nEnsure all date displays throughout the gallery webpage respect the user's selected language preference, eliminating any hardcoded English date formats.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit all date instances on the gallery webpage to identify English-formatted dates\n- Replace hardcoded English date formats with locale-aware formatting functions\n- Ensure date formatting dynamically updates when user changes language selector\n- Apply consistent date format pattern across all gallery date displays (e.g., image upload dates, metadata timestamps, creation dates)\n- Handle various date formats appropriately: short dates, long dates, relative dates (e.g., \"2 days ago\")\n- Test date display with multiple target languages from the language selector\n- Verify month names, day names, and date ordering match selected locale conventions\n- Ensure timezone handling remains consistent across localization",
  "title": "Implement locale-aware date formatting across gallery",
